# Project Structure

DOOH Network V1 monorepo — Digital Out-of-Home advertising marketplace.

## Layout

```
doohbg/
├── apps/
│   ├── api/              # NestJS REST API + webhooks + cron
│   ├── web/              # Next.js marketplace + /admin
│   └── player-android/   # Kotlin Android TV player
├── packages/
│   ├── db/               # Prisma schema, migrations, seed
│   ├── shared/           # Zod schemas, booking state machine, constants
│   └── config/           # Shared tsconfig
├── infra/docker-compose.yml
├── docs/adr/             # Architecture decision records
└── docb/DOOH_Network_V1_PRD.md
```

## Key commands

```bash
pnpm install
docker compose -f infra/docker-compose.yml up -d
cp .env.example .env
pnpm db:generate && pnpm db:migrate && pnpm db:seed
pnpm dev
```

## Conventions

- Read `docb/DOOH_Network_V1_PRD.md` before implementing features.
- Player is **native Kotlin** (not RN/Flutter).
- Double-booking: `slot_occupancy` unique on `(device_id, slot_index, play_date)`.
- Liveness: 60s heartbeat; marketplace hides stale devices in production.
